By cssSelector
=============================
- CssSelector is Locator which identify element based on Css properties(css id,attribute,classname)
- CssSelector is cleaner & faster than xpath
- CssSelector is faster as it can travel from Parent tag to child tag
- CssSelector does not support text based element identification
- Csselector does not have any method but we can identify element uniquely based on 
special symbols

CssSelector Basics
-------------------------
1.tagname with id
--------------------
Syntax:
==========
tagname#id

Example:
<a id="SignIn" name="sign-in-link" class="nav-link" href="login.html">Sign In</a>

a#SignIn
OR
#SignIn
---------------------------------------------------
2.tagname with attribute
--------------------------------
Syntax:
==============
tagname[attribute='value']

Example:
<input  type="email" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter email" required="">

input[type='email'].....1 of 1

--------------------------------------------------------
3.tagname with className
------------------------------
cssSelector class name support multiple class names

Syntax:
=============
tagname.className

Example:
<button class="btn btn-default btn-primary">Submit</button>

button.btn.btn-default.btn-primary     1 of 1

-------------------------------------------------------
4.tagname with id,attribute and className
------------------------------------------------
Syntax:
=============
tagname#id.className[attribute='value']

Example:
<button id="submit-id" name="submit-name" class="btn btn-default btn-primary">Submit</button>

button#submit-id.btn[name='submit-name']

