Assertions
---------------
-To validate current status of application we perform assertion
-Assertions are used to verify whether the actual result matches the expected result. 
-If the assertion fails, the test may stop or continue depending on the assertion type.

Selenium support two types of assertion

1.Hard Assertion
---------------------
-A Hard Assertion immediately stops the execution of the test when an assertion fails.
-Any statements after the failed assertion are not executed.
-Hard Assertion we can implement using Assert class

2.Soft Assertion
-------------------------
-A Soft Assertion allows the test execution to continue even if an assertion fails.
-All assertion failures are collected and reported at the end using assertAll().
-Soft Assertion we can implement using SoftAssert class
