TestNG XML File (testng.xml)
==============================================
-The testng.xml file is a configuration file in TestNG used to control how your test cases
are executed. 
-Instead of running individual test classes manually, you can use testng.xml 
to execute multiple test classes, create test suites, run tests in parallel,
pass parameters, and much more.
 
With testng.xml:
==========================
Execute multiple test classes at once.
Group test cases.
Control execution order.
Run tests in parallel.
Pass parameters.
Include or exclude specific tests.
Configure listeners.

